OTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Coming from the old world of Dungeons and Dragons, one of the first characters I started on EverQuest was a warrior.  A troll warrior to be exact.  My days in DnD had taught me that the most fierce and powerful melee class was the warrior.  No other melee class struck fear in the hearts of man and monster like the warrior did.  The warrior, be it a small but mighty dwarf or an over powering barbarian, was someone to be reckoned with and not to be taken lightly.  So, I sat out on my quest to build a mighty warrior on EverQuest.  And so Bigemnose Andhow the Troll Warrior was born.<br>
<br>
Now in my 48th season as a warrior, I find myself questioning myself.  For what I had known in DnD as the master of melee damage has turned out to be a low damage but fast agro holding punching bag for the mobs.  What is this EQ warrior that I see before me?  My only purpose in life seems to be hitting the monster as fast as I can and doing very littel damage while at the same time getting the living crap beat out of me and only living because I have a cleric constantly healing me.  Where is my fear inspiring killing machine of a warrior?  Does it not exist in EQ?  Did the designers of EQ not truely understand the definition of a warrior when they made this game?  What happened?<br>
<br>
Why am I as a warrior forced to carry two weapons that have a crappy damage of 9 just because they have a delay of 19?  Shouldn't I be wielding something that does more like 100 dmaage per swing and making a complete mess of the monsters that stand in my wake?  And, why am I getting the crap beat out of me by these mobs?  I am a fierce monster of a warrior, am I not?  So, why am I getting knocked to hell and back by the monsters?????<br>
<br>
Is there one man or woman here who actually played DnD and/or has read hundreds of paperback fantasy books that can honestly tell me that a true warrior had to drag a healer with him in to ever dungeon he went in?  This should not be the case.  If it was, then the warrior was nothing more then an idiot with a sword.  I want my Conan... I want my Caramon... I want my WARRIOR!<br>
